tication, authorization, tool schema, tool execution, failure handling, and audit evidence before integrating with a real MCP service.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:22:| `/endpoints/new` | Create one mock MCP/REST tool |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:25:| `/endpoints/[id]/parameters` | Up to three parameters and generated MCP `inputSchema` |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:28:| `/endpoints/[id]/console` | REST/MCP-style execution evidence |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:35:| `/config` | Effective base URL, health, MCP/REST/OAuth/TLS connection URLs |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:45:| Streamable HTTP MCP | `/mcp`, `/mcp/none`, `/mcp/basic`, `/mcp/oauth` | Modern JSON-RPC MCP over HTTP POST. GET returns a lightweight SSE stream for compatibility checks. |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:46:| Legacy SSE MCP | `/sse`, `/sse/none`, `/sse/basic`, `/sse/oauth` | Inspector-compatible SSE stream that emits an `endpoint` event for POSTing messages. |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:65:Each endpoint becomes an MCP tool and a REST-callable mock operation.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:74:- generated MCP `inputSchema`\ndocs/FEATURES.md:87:- forced REST/MCP error\ndocs/FEATURES.md:97:MCP Mock Server provides three verification paths:\ndocs/FEATURES.md:101:- **Upstream MCP Inspector**: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector`.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:103:The standalone project Inspector is the easiest way to prove the full Mock Server product flow. The upstream Inspector is best for standard MCP protocol debugging and compatibility checks.\ntests/e2e/basic-auth-mcp.spec.ts:7:test(\"Basic Auth MCP strict route and unified precedence fail closed and allow valid callers @basic-auth-mcp\", async ({\ntests/e2e/basic-auth-mcp.spec.ts:18:      title: \"Basic MCP endpoint\",\ntests/e2e/basic-auth-mcp.spec.ts:19:      description: \"Callable through Basic-authenticated MCP routes.\",\ntests/e2e/basic-auth-mcp.spec.ts:67:    data: { jsonrpc: \"2.0\", id: \"missing\", method: \"tools/list\" },\ntests/e2e/basic-auth-mcp.spec.ts:74:    data: { jsonrpc: \"2.0\", id: \"malformed\", method: \"tools/list\