ity expectations and failure-handling rules for MCP Mock Server.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:13:- resource and prompt runtime responses must use the same JSON-RPC adapter and auth precedence as tools so full MCP feature coverage does not create a second protocol path\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:28:## MCP No-Auth Runtime\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:29:- `/mcp` without credentials and `/mcp/none` must share the same no-auth MCP adapter so client examples do not drift.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:30:- The first runtime slice is stateless: `initialize` does not create an MCP session, `notifications/initialized` returns `202` with no body, and unsupported SSE/session methods return `405` with `Allow: POST`.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:31:- `tools/list` must read enabled endpoints from the endpoint domain service and use the shared generated MCP input schema helper; disabled endpoints must remain hidden.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:34:## MCP Resources And Prompts Runtime\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:35:- `resources/list`, `resources/templates/list`, `resources/read`, `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and `completion/complete` must be covered by protocol unit tests before capability advertisement is expanded.\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:61:- SSE streaming and MCP sessions are Phase 2\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:1:# MCP Transports, REST, SSE, And OAuth Calls\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:3:This page gives copy-ready protocol calls for MCP Mock Server.\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:9:| Mode | Streamable HTTP MCP | Legacy SSE MCP | REST |\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:30:  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"initialize\",\"params\":{\"protocolVersion\":\"2025-06-18\",\"capabilities\":{},\"clientInfo\":{\"name\":\"curl\",\"version\":\"1.0.0\"}}}'\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:39:  -H 'MCP-Protocol-Version: 2025-06-18' \\\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:40:  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"method\":\"tools/list\"}'\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:49:  -H 'MCP-Protocol-Version: 2025-06-18' \\\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:60:  -H 'MCP-Protocol-Version: 2025-06-18' \\\ndocs/TRANSPORTS.md:61:  -d '{\"json