oken, and revocation routes answer browser preflight `OPTIONS` requests with HTTP `204`, `Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, DELETE, OPTIONS`, and allow the standard MCP test headers, including `Authorization`, `Content-Type`, `Last-Event-ID`, `MCP-Session-Id`, and `MCP-Protocol-Version`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:28:- MCP clients should send `Accept: application/json, text/event-stream`; the MVP server is lenient and does not reject missing `Accept` headers because many manual test clients omit them.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:29:- `initialize` returns protocol version `2025-06-18` when requested, otherwise the newest MVP-supported version from `2025-06-18` and `2025-03-26`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:30:- `initialize` advertises only the `tools` capability with `listChanged: false`; resources, prompts, logging, sampling, durable session, and resumability capabilities are not claimed.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:32:- `notifications/initialized` is accepted as a JSON-RPC notification with HTTP `202` and no response body.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:33:- `tools/list` returns enabled endpoint tools only, with each tool's name, description, and generated endpoint-domain `inputSchema`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:34:- `tools/list` for valid OAuth Bearer callers returns only enabled endpoint tools included in the token's endpoint permissions.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:35:- `tools/call` on `/mcp` without credentials and `/mcp/none` executes enabled endpoints by name through the shared endpoint matcher. Exact response cases return MCP tool results with text content, and JSON-object responses also return `structuredContent`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md:38:- Configured endpoint or response-case delays apply before MCP tool success, tool-error, or protocol-error responses and are bounded to 30000 ms.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runti